cs.DM, cs.AI, cs.CE, cs.LG, cs.NE

Reasoning: 
- cs.DM (Discrete Mathematics) is the most likely category as the paper deals with optimization of quadratic unconstrained binary optimization (QUBO) problems, which is a discrete optimization problem. 
- cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) is also likely as the paper presents a meta-heuristic solver that utilizes a quantum annealer to solve larger or denser problems. 
- cs.CE (Computational Engineering, Finance, and Science) is another possible category as the paper discusses the practical use of the solver and the dependence of the time to best solution on the desired gap to the best known solution. 
- cs.LG (Machine Learning) is a possible category as the paper presents a solver that uses a machine learning approach to iteratively solve subproblems. 
- cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) is another possible category as the paper presents a meta-heuristic solver that uses an evolutionary approach to iteratively solve subproblems.
